abstract: NASHVILLE, July 9--The temperature reached 105 degrees on the 18th green at the Richland Country Club today, with high humidity and no relief predicted for the next four days. Those are the four days when the 35th United States Women's Open golf championship will be held on the 6,299-yard course.

abstract: NOBLESVILLE, Ind., July 6 (AP)-- Amy Alcott withstood the challenges of Sally Little and Joanne Carner today, shot a 69 for 275, and posted her 11th Ladies Professional Golf Association victory in the $150,000 Mayflower Classic.
WASHINGTON, July 6--After six months in which he barely strayed from the White House because of the Iranian crisis, President Carter seems to have been bitten by the travel bug.
headline_main: For President, Trips Resume At Quick Pace

abstract: Somebody else will be handling the seating at Carnegie Hall Tuesday night because nearly one-third of the ushering staff will be onstage demonstrating that their involvement in music goes far beyond handing out programs.

abstract: OAK BROOK, Ill., July 5 (AP)-- Scott Simpson overcame the wind to shoot a two-under-par 70 today, which gave him a 54-hole total of 209 and a five-stroke lead in the 77th Western open golf tournament.
